{"type":"message","id":"201cfd64","parentId":"802fbf56","timestamp":"2026-03-27T03:23:09.221Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Telegram is already configured with a bot token and enabled. The `dmPolicy` is set to \"pairing\", which means the bot needs to be paired. Let me check what the pairing process looks like - the user likely needs to message the bot on Telegram and then confirm the pairing.\n\nLet me check the status to see if Telegram is actually connected and working.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Good news — Telegram is already configured with a bot token and enabled. The bot's `dmPolicy` is set to \"pairing\", which means you need to connect your Telegram account to it.\n\nHere's how to get linked up:\n\n1. **Find your bot on Telegram** — search for it by the bot username associated with the token (do you know the bot's username? I can check if needed)\n2. **Send `/start`** to the bot in Telegram\n3. It should trigger a pairing flow — you'll get a code or prompt to confirm\n\nThe bot's already enabled and waiting. Want me to check the bot's username or look into anything else about the setup?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"kilo-auto/free","usage":{"input":3328,"output":291,"cacheRead":22144,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":25763,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774581766689}}
