{"type":"message","id":"e4019e77","parentId":"8ef90af1","timestamp":"2026-03-27T03:24:31.513Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Only one session showing - the webchat one. No Telegram session appeared. The bot might not be properly connected, or there could be an issue with the bot token or webhook. Let me check if there are any relevant docs about Telegram pairing setup.\n\nThe `dmPolicy` is set to \"pairing\" which means the bot needs to be paired with a specific user. When the user sends /start, it should generate a pairing code. But \"nothing happened\" suggests the bot might not be responding at all.\n\nLet me check the node-connect skill since it mentions pairing issues.\n\nActually, looking at the config again, the Telegram bot is configured and enabled. The issue might be that the bot needs to be linked/paired. Let me look at how pairing works.\n\n\nI should check the gateway logs to see what's actually happening when the user tries to interact with the bot.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Only one session showing — no Telegram connection yet. Let me check if the bot is actually responding. The config has `dmPolicy: \"pairing\"` so you might need a pairing code. Let me dig deeper."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_1b909aafb4474ef9a551b400","name":"gateway","arguments":{"action":"config.schema.lookup","path":"channels.telegram"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"kilo-auto/free","usage":{"input":650,"output":432,"cacheRead":26240,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":27322,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774581854813}}
