{"type":"message","id":"cb59157e","parentId":"a266a571","timestamp":"2026-03-27T03:25:09.889Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The openclaw status output seems truncated. It's showing a session table but I can't see the full output. Let me look at what was returned. The output seems to be cut off. Let me check what's visible:\n\nThe output shows a session list with agent:main:main and the model kilo-auto/free with cache stats. But I don't see anything about Telegram channel status.\n\nThe output is truncated. I can only see the session table. The Telegram channel status would be in a different section of the output. Let me ask the user to check specifically for Telegram status or try to help them with what I can see.\n\nActually, looking at the output more carefully, it seems like the user just shared the tail end of the `openclaw status` output. The important parts about channel status might be above the truncation point. Let me ask them to look specifically for Telegram in the output, or check the Telegram bot configuration more carefully.\n\n\nI need to focus on the Telegram bot token and whether the gateway has actually configured the webhook for it, since I can't run diagnostics directly to verify this.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Hmm, the output got cut off — I'm only seeing the session table. Can you scroll up in the `openclaw status` output and look for a section about **channels** or **Telegram**? Specifically something like:\n\n- `telegram: connected` or `disconnected`\n- Any errors about Telegram or webhooks\n\nOr try this more targeted command:\n\n```bash\nopenclaw status 2>&1 | grep -i -A5 telegram\n```\n\nThat'll pull just the Telegram-related lines. Share whatever it shows — even if it says \"not found\" or errors out, that tells us something."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"kilo-auto/free","usage":{"input":3410,"output":584,"cacheRead":19520,"cacheWrite"