{"type":"message","id":"c07bf426","parentId":"395adcfb","timestamp":"2026-03-27T03:25:22.645Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Streamchat doesn't support chat exec approvals. I need to ask the user to run the command themselves since I can't get exec approval through this channel.\n\nLet me just ask the user to run the command themselves.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Ah, I can't run exec commands through this chat channel — they need to be approved through the web UI or terminal. You'll need to run that one yourself:\n\n```bash\nopenclaw status 2>&1 | grep -i -A5 telegram\n```\n\nPaste the output here and I'll help figure out what's going on. The issue is likely that the Telegram bot isn't actually polling for updates from Telegram's servers, even though the config looks correct on our end."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"kilo-auto/free","usage":{"input":123,"output":189,"cacheRead":23488,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":23800,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774581915473}}
