{"type":"message","id":"6b95300e","parentId":"365e15c6","timestamp":"2026-03-27T03:25:36.595Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see the output now. It shows:\n- Stream Chat: ON | OK | configured\n\nBut I don't see Telegram in the output at all. This means the Telegram channel is not showing up as active/connected. It might be configured but not actually connected/running.\n\nLet me ask the user to run a command that shows ALL channels, including Telegram status.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Got it — I can see Stream Chat is ON and OK, but **Telegram isn't showing up in the channels list at all**. That means the Telegram channel isn't connected, even though it's configured.\n\nThe config looks right (token, enabled, all that), but the gateway probably hasn't established the connection to Telegram's servers. \n\nTry restarting the gateway — that should force it to reconnect to Telegram:\n\n```bash\nopenclaw gateway restart\n```\n\nAfter it restarts, try `/start` in the bot again. If it still doesn't work, we'll dig deeper into whether the bot token is valid and the webhook is set up.\n\nLet me know what happens! ⚡"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"kilo-auto/free","usage":{"input":394,"output":296,"cacheRead":23552,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":24242,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774581925728}}
